{#- Changelog — one `### v<N>` section per entry in `changelog[]`, newest first.
    Every bullet is structured and factual. The `note` field is rendered only
    when there is no structured delta to show (v1 initial assessment or
    `--rebuild`) — it is not used as a free-form prose summary.

    Data shape per entry (see schemas/threat-model.output.schema.yaml):
      version, date, mode, baseline_sha, current_sha
      changed_files, changed_lines ({insertions, deletions})
      added:    { threats: [T-NNN,...], mitigations: [M-NNN,...],
                  abuse_cases: [AC-NNN,...], components: [C-NN,...], attack_surface: [E-NN,...] }
      changed:  { threats: [T-NNN,...], notes_by_id:   { T-NNN: "..." } }
      resolved: { threats: [T-NNN,...], reason_by_id:  { T-NNN: "..." } }
      reanalyzed_components, carried_forward_components, note

    Detail cap: inline T-ID enumeration capped at `_max` with a "+N more" suffix.
    The yaml persists the full list — the cap only bounds the rendered markdown.
    Mirrors `_sample_ids` in scripts/render_completion_summary.py. -#}
{%- set _max = 5 -%}
## Changelog

_Append-only history of assessment runs. Most recent first._
{% for entry in changelog %}
{%- set v             = entry.version -%}
{%- set date          = entry.date or '—' -%}
{%- set mode          = (entry.mode or 'full') | lower -%}
{%- set baseline_sha  = entry.baseline_sha or '' -%}
{%- set current_sha   = entry.current_sha or '' -%}
{%- set has_baseline  = (baseline_sha | length) > 0 -%}
{%- set short_base    = baseline_sha[:7] -%}
{%- set short_cur     = current_sha[:7] if current_sha else '—' -%}
{%- set added         = entry.added or {} -%}
{%- set changed       = entry.changed or {} -%}
{%- set resolved      = entry.resolved or {} -%}
{%- set a_t           = added.threats or [] -%}
{%- set a_m           = added.mitigations or [] -%}
{%- set a_ac          = added.abuse_cases or [] -%}
{%- set a_c           = added.components or [] -%}
{%- set a_e           = added.attack_surface or [] -%}
{%- set c_t           = changed.threats or [] -%}
{%- set c_n           = changed.notes_by_id or {} -%}
{%- set r_t           = resolved.threats or [] -%}
{%- set r_r           = resolved.reason_by_id or {} -%}
{%- set a_t_shown     = a_t[:_max] -%}
{%- set a_t_extra     = (a_t|length) - (a_t_shown|length) -%}
{%- set a_m_shown     = a_m[:_max] -%}
{%- set a_m_extra     = (a_m|length) - (a_m_shown|length) -%}
{%- set a_ac_shown    = a_ac[:_max] -%}
{%- set a_ac_extra    = (a_ac|length) - (a_ac_shown|length) -%}
{%- set c_t_shown     = c_t[:_max] -%}
{%- set c_t_extra     = (c_t|length) - (c_t_shown|length) -%}
{%- set r_t_shown     = r_t[:_max] -%}
{%- set r_t_extra     = (r_t|length) - (r_t_shown|length) -%}
{%- set reanalyzed    = entry.reanalyzed_components or [] -%}
{%- set carried       = entry.carried_forward_components or [] -%}
{%- set changed_files = entry.changed_files -%}
{%- set changed_lines = entry.changed_lines or {} -%}
{%- set ins           = changed_lines.insertions -%}
{%- set dels          = changed_lines.deletions -%}
{%- set note          = (entry.note or '') | trim -%}
{#- Defensive truncation: the orchestrator is instructed to emit short factual
    notes only (≤12 words, see phase-group-finalization.md §"note guidance").
    Long prose is truncated here so a single run cannot clutter the section. -#}
{%- if (note | length) > 100 -%}{%- set note = note[:98] ~ '…' -%}{%- endif -%}
{%- if has_baseline %}
### v{{ v }} — {{ date }} ({{ mode }}, baseline `{{ short_base }}` → `{{ short_cur }}`)
{%- elif v == 1 and mode == 'full' %}
### v{{ v }} — {{ date }} ({{ mode }} — initial assessment)
{%- else %}
### v{{ v }} — {{ date }} ({{ mode }})
{%- endif %}
{% if has_baseline -%}
{%- if changed_files is not none and changed_files %}
- **Changed files:** {{ changed_files }}{% if ins is not none and dels is not none %} (+{{ ins }}/-{{ dels }} lines){% endif %}
{%- endif %}
{%- if a_t %}
- **Added:** {{ a_t|length }} {{ 'threat' if a_t|length == 1 else 'threats' }} ({% for tid in a_t_shown %}[{{ tid }}](#{{ tid|lower }}){% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}{% if a_t_extra > 0 %}, +{{ a_t_extra }} more{% endif %})
{%- endif %}
{%- if c_t %}
- **Changed:** {{ c_t|length }} {{ 'threat' if c_t|length == 1 else 'threats' }} ({% for tid in c_t_shown %}[{{ tid }}](#{{ tid|lower }}){% if tid in c_n %}: "{{ c_n[tid] }}"{% endif %}{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}{% if c_t_extra > 0 %}, +{{ c_t_extra }} more{% endif %})
{%- endif %}
{%- if r_t %}
- **Resolved:** {{ r_t|length }} {{ 'threat' if r_t|length == 1 else 'threats' }} ({% for tid in r_t_shown %}[{{ tid }}](#{{ tid|lower }}){% if tid in r_r %}: "{{ r_r[tid] }}"{% endif %}{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}{% if r_t_extra > 0 %}, +{{ r_t_extra }} more{% endif %})
{%- endif %}
{%- if a_m %}
- **New mitigations:** {{ a_m|length }} ({% for mid in a_m_shown %}[{{ mid }}](#{{ mid|lower }}){% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}{% if a_m_extra > 0 %}, +{{ a_m_extra }} more{% endif %})
{%- endif %}
{%- if a_ac %}
- **New abuse cases:** {{ a_ac|length }} ({% for ac in a_ac_shown %}[{{ ac }}](#{{ ac|lower }}){% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}{% if a_ac_extra > 0 %}, +{{ a_ac_extra }} more{% endif %})
{%- endif %}
{%- if a_c or a_e %}
- **Architecture:**{% if a_c %} +{{ a_c|length }} {{ 'component' if a_c|length == 1 else 'components' }} ({{ a_c|join(', ') }}){% endif %}{% if a_c and a_e %},{% endif %}{% if a_e %} +{{ a_e|length }} {{ 'entry point' if a_e|length == 1 else 'entry points' }} ({{ a_e|join(', ') }}){% endif %}
{%- endif %}
{%- if reanalyzed %}
- **Re-analyzed:** {{ reanalyzed|join(', ') }}
{%- endif %}
{%- if carried %}
- **Carried forward:** {{ carried|join(', ') }}
{%- endif %}
{%- if note and (note|lower) != 'initial assessment' %}
- {{ note }}
{%- endif %}
{%- elif note and not (v == 1 and mode == 'full' and (note|lower) == 'initial assessment') %}

- {{ note }}
{%- endif %}
{% endfor %}
